<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-08-03T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-08-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="646" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/559: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GSE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grummon</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-08-03T19:00:00-04:00">August 3,
                                    1939—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>113. Your 417, July 31, 10 p.m. Was it your impression that <persName corresp="#p_MAI1">Mikoyan</persName> meant that the Soviet
                            Government was not interested in obtaining tariff reductions in
                            connection with a possible trade agreement or did he merely intend to
                            inform you that the Soviet Government would not pursue the matter in
                            connection with this commercial agreement? Please do not raise the
                            question with Soviet officials.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WS1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>